[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scunthorpe United: Ivan Toney and Matt Crooks join on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One side Scunthorpe have signed Newcastle striker Ivan Toney and Glasgow Rangers midfielder Matt Crooks on loan until the end of the season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Toney recently returned to Newcastle after a loan spell with Shrewsbury, where he scored seven goals in 26 games in all competitions.
The 20-year-old had been linked with a return to former club Northampton.
Crooks, 22, has played three games for Scottish Premiership side Rangers since joining from Accrington in July.
